&nbsp;
<h2> Migration flows
The government has never wanted to reintroduce the <a href="https://www.agi.it/politica/news/2024-05-25/duello-distance-meloni-schlein-festival-trento-26518981/">reditometro</a>. "It is said that the government has reintroduced a mechanism of great fiscal brother. It's not like that. We are opposed to the very clear income meter on the left", notes the premier who then recalls the need to fix stakes to the synthetic ascertainment that "continue to exist". The objective is to establish the limits to a ascertainment that "it is entirely arbitrary and discretionary", for the premier it is "a dangerous situation", hence the genesis of the "ministerial decree that had been prepared". "We compared ourselves with Deputy Minister Leo and came to the conclusion of suspending" the decree - Meloni has remembered - "we took some time" to "ensure greater guarantees to the taxpayers and to work to a different norm on which there are two hypotheses: to overcome the principle of synthetic ascertainment or to work on a rule that circumscribes this instrument to unacceptable phenomena, without vexing common citizens." "The goal is to create a fisco friend" that does not contain "astroyed norms and an unbearable level of taxation". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"The landings in Italy continue to decline, to date with respect to the period of the same year almost 60% decreased. These are data that must improve and improve. The greater satisfaction comes from the agreement with Albania," he explains on immigration. "A few days ago - it has observed - fifteen European countries on twenty-seven, therefore, the majority of European countries has signed an appeal to the European Commission on immigration in which among other things it is written that the EU must follow the Italian model of the agreement with Albania. The letter says that we must build models like those of the protocol between Italy and Albania. In short, with good peace of the left of our country and its attempts to make any response to the illegal immigration front fail. Italy on immigration is doing school."
&nbsp;
<h2>House and birth
"The last Council of Ministers has approved a rule which I consider of absolute common sense that will allow to give answer to a series of housing needs and also to give a little breath to the real estate market that today is in suffering and we want to help to relaunch," said the premier. "The norm basically allows to remedy the small and slight differences that today lie in the houses of many Italians and that prevent to sell or buy those real estate because they are formally considered irregular. Of course, we do not speak of building abuse which - it has remembered - none of us intends to heal, to scans of misunderstandings and contrary to what the opposition says, but we speak of small irregularities mostly formal and bureaucratic that today do not allow you to sell your house or to restructure it and sometimes to buy one". "As for us the house is sacred and for many Italians it is also the investment of a life, I think that if you have a house it is right that you can sell it without the state to prevent it for matters of goat wool, especially when you ask to heal those slight internal difformities the same state does not respond to you for months and in some cases for years," he concluded.
&nbsp;
"Among the great objectives there has always been the support for birth and the unique check is one of the most effective tools to favor it. We kept it and invested 3 billion euros more. I am talking about it because the European Commission has decided to open an infringement procedure with crazy reasons," Meloni said, repeating what he had said yesterday at the Trento economic festival. "If we were to follow the EU's indications, the measure would be unsustainable and would be prepared for different scams. I hope that the next Commission will have a more reasonable approach, if that is not the case," he said.
&nbsp;
"I want to conclude" this video with "a question to be addressed to the secretary of the Pd Elly Schlein.> The secretary of the PD recently said that in this year and a half I would be erasing the freedom of people, singular accusation for those who voted to close people in the house during the pandemic", the premise, "between serious people, when an accusation moves especially if it is so heavy you must be in the condition of argumenting it. I want to ask Schlein what freedoms are erased by this government and what measures." "For what I see is that we are reforming this system to allow," for example, "the citizens to vote for the head of government while the left is against," said Meloni. "Ours are battles of freedom. Tell us what the freedoms we would have erased," he said. "Tell us what he speaks but tell us something concrete" because "freedom has always been limited only to the left and the point is that citizens have understood it", he concluded.&nbsp;&nbsp;
